5
00:00:27,609 --> 00:00:34,460
Most of the time, through our language development, there&#39;s very few errors happening, but children

6
00:00:34,460 --> 00:00:40,820
make these referential errors in the first 50 words or so and they’re quite interesting.

7
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:44,620
The first kind of error is called an overextension error.

8
00:00:44,620 --> 00:00:48,610
Chamberlain &amp; Chamberlain looked at this in 1904.

9
00:00:48,610 --> 00:00:54,280
This is where you have a word that refers to one thing and babies overextend the reference

10
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,280
(Chamberlain &amp; Chamberlain, 1904).

11
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:59,481
For example, you&#39;ve got a little 14-month old, her daddy takes her out regularly, they

12
00:00:59,481 --> 00:01:04,010
